description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen with our Assessment and Treatment service as a Medical Secretary to join our medical admin team to provide support to a Consultant Psychiatrist, Specialty Doctor and Junior Doctors.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;About you:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be a resilient and experienced Medical Secretary or secretary with a can do attitude. You must be able to work flexibly, have excellent communication skills and have the ability to manage competing priorities along with attention to detail.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be responsible for diary management, transcribing clinic letters, managing appointments and liaising with our service users and supporting them with queries and arranging for the electronic safe delivery of prescriptions to pharmacies. You will also support the team with managing key performance indicators such as waiting times and Care Plan data.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lindsey Jones&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Business Administration Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tel: 07912 554473&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email: lindsey.jones@sussexpartnership.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
